Proteas fast bowler Kagiso Rabada encourages South Africans to stay #HealthyAtHome. JOHANNESBURG - Proteas fast bowler Kagiso Rabada has encouraged South Africans to stay healthy at home during the lockdown. South Africa has been under a nationwide lockdown since late March in a bid to curb the spread of the coronavirus. Under lockdown regulations, jogging and going to the gym has been prohibited. WATCH: Ramaphosa responds after mask mishap This has left many frustrated, however, Rabada enlisted the assistance of some South African celebrities to help spread the message of staying healthy at home. In the end, the celebrities challenge the rest of the country to do the same.